{
  "title": "Implementing Cron-Driven Tasks Using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide demonstrates how to set up and run cron-style scheduled tasks using the FastAPI framework in Python 3.12+, along with APScheduler for task scheduling.",

  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI is a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.7+.",
    "APScheduler is an event scheduler library that lets you schedule functions or methods to run later.",
    "This example demonstrates how to integrate APScheduler into a FastAPI application for cron-style scheduled tasks."
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\nfrom apscheduler.schedulers.background import BackgroundScheduler\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\nscheduler = BackgroundScheduler()\n\ndef scheduled_task():\n    # Your task code here\n\nscheduler.add_job(scheduled_task, 'cron', hour='*/12')\nscheduler.start()\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    import uvicorn\n    uvicorn.run(app, host='0.0.0.0', port=8000)\n```"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "This example is designed for Python 3.12+ and utilizes FastAPI v0.70.0.",
    "Updates to the framework or library versions may require adjustments to the code."
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Remember to install APScheduler with `pip install apscheduler` before running the example.",
    "This example demonstrates a simple scheduled task. Real-world applications may require more complex scheduling, error handling, and integration with databases or external services."
  ]
}
